      </p>
      <p>where â<italic>E</italic><sub><italic>ij</italic></sub>â is the integer part of the expected number and <italic>Î´</italic><sub><italic>ij</italic></sub> is the fractal part. In the case of equalbatch size, it reduces to <inline-formula><mml:math id="M2" name="1471-2164-13-689-i2" overflow="scroll"><mml:mrow><mml:mfenced open="â" close="â"><mml:msub><mml:mi>E</mml:mi><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">ij</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:mfenced><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mfrac><mml:msub><mml:mi>S</mml:mi><mml:mi>j</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mi>m</mml:mi></mml:mfrac></mml:mrow></mml:math></inline-formula> . When we have RCBD, all <italic>Î´</italic><sub><italic>ij</italic></sub> are zero.</p>
      <p>For an actual sample assignment</p>
      <p>
